<div id="intro">
<h1>Introduction</h1>
<p><span style="font-size:3em; float:left; line-height:1; padding:0 0.15em 0 0;">N</span>ational Institute of Agrobiological Sciences
(<a href="http://www.nias.affrc.go.jp/index_e.html">NIAS</a>)
produced a total of 35,189 EST sequences of Magnaporthe grisea. The NIAS ESTs were mapped on genome supercontigs and assembled using
<a href="http://pasa.sourceforge.net/">PASA</a>.
To fill gaps between the EST pairs and construct complete CDSs, transcript sequences in a public database and ab initio gene prediction program were also used.</p>

<p>All data are integrated to a widely used genome viewer,
<a href="http://gmod.org/wiki/GBrowse">GBrowse</a>.
Click "GBrowse" link at the top of this page.</p>
</div>

<div id="ref">
<h1>Reference</h1>
<p>EST statistics and assembly method are described in:</p>
<ul>
<li>Numa, H., Nishimura, M., Tanaka, T., Kanamori, H., Yang, C., Matsumoto, T., Nagamura, Y., Itoh, T. (2009) Genome-wide validation of Magnaporthe grisea gene structures based on transcription evidence. <a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.febslet.2009.01.041">FEBS Lett. 583, 797-800.</a></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

